The Marketplace requirements for apps with app cards are described and/or hyperlinked <https://developers.HubSpot.com/beta-docs/guides/crm/public-apps/overview#app-marketplace-guidelines|here>. As a certified app, you should ensure all of the <https://developers.HubSpot.com/beta-docs/guides/apps/marketplace/certification-requirements|certification requirements> are still being met.

For convenience, I'll copy it below:
&gt; *Add UI extensions to an existing listed app*
&gt; 
&gt; Follow <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/platform/migrate-a-public-app-to-projects|this guide> to migrate your existing listed app to the projects framework. Once successfully converted, reference <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/platform/build-ui-extensions-for-public-apps|this guide> and its linked resources to create and deploy UI extensions.
&gt; 
&gt; Use <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/platform/migrate-a-public-app-to-projects#feature-flag-api|feature flags> to release these UI extensions to up to 5 test or customer accounts. You will be unable to release the app cards to more accounts until Ecosystem Quality has confirmed your new app cards meet <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/platform/build-ui-extensions-for-public-apps#app-marketplace-guidelines|these additional guidelines>. Email your app ID, most recent build ID, developer Hub ID, test account ID, and instructions on locating your app card in the test account to <mailto:app-card-review@HubSpot.com|app-card-review@HubSpot.com> to start this process.
&gt; 
&gt; Once approved, <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/listing-your-app#edit-a-live-app-listing|edit your app listing> to highlight the new app cards. Once your listing has been updated, it will be added to a Marketplace collection of apps which have similarly enabled UI extensions. Finally, leverage feature flags to release app cards to your install base at your pace and discretion.
